  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a full kettle</p><p>Chop your<strong> potatoes</strong> into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Chop your<strong> cherry tomatoes</strong> in half</p><p>Trim your <strong>green beans</strong></p><p>Crush your <strong>garlic</strong> open by squashing it with the side of a knife and discard the skins</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1724065992751-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1724065992751-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1724065992751-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1724065992751-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1724065992751-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> chopped potatoes</strong> to a pot with plenty of <strong>boiled water </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, cook for an initial 10 min</p><p>After 10 min, add the <strong>green beans</strong> to the pot</p><p>Cook the potatoes and green beans together for a further 5-7 min, or until tender</p><p>Once tender, drain and allow to cool slightly</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1724066001190-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1724066001190-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1724066001190-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1724066001190-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1724066001190-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the potatoes are cooking, heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick, with a matching lid) with a drizzle of<strong> olive oil </strong>over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>halved tomatoes </strong>to the pan and cook for for 3 min or until they are blistered - these are your <strong>blistered tomatoes</strong></p><p>Once the tomatoes are blistered transfer them to a plate and reserve the pan for later</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1724066019609-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1724066019609-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1724066019609-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1724066019609-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1724066019609-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine your<strong> pesto </strong>and <strong>half</strong> your <strong>balsamic vinegar </strong>(save the rest for later!) in a large bowl with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp] </span><strong>cold water</strong>, a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper </strong>– this is your <strong>balsamic</strong> <strong>pesto dressing</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1200.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1200.-step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1200.-step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1200.-step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1200.-step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Wipe the reserved pan with some kitchen paper and return it to a medium-high heat with a drizzle of<strong> olive oil</strong></p><p>Pat your <strong>sea bass</strong> dry and season on both sides with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>seasoned sea bass fillet[s]</strong>, skin side down with the <strong>crushed garlic</strong> and cook for 5 min, then flip the sea bass and cook for 1 min further or until cooked through</p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1724066106757-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
